Sec. 8. That when said bridge shall be completed, said company shall be authorized to demand and receive the fol-
lowing rates of toll, viz: For every loaded wagon and six horses, mules or oxen, one dollar, and ten cents for each pair of animals additional; for every loaded wagon and four horses, mules or oxen, seventy-five cents; for every loaded wagon and two horses, mules or oxen, fifty cents, and one-half the above rates for any of the above wagons if empty; for any vehicle drawn by one horse, mule or ox, twenty-five cents each way; for every horseman, ten cents;
Laws of the State of Texas.for every footman, five cents; for every head of loose horses, mules or cattle, five cents each; and for sheep, hogs or goats, two and one-half cents each.
